Clean type-check. Here's what was done:

## Changes Summary

### New: glow tuning tokens (`tokens.css`)
- **`--eva-glow-rgb`**: Raw RGB channels (`204, 136, 0` default) — theme-aware, overridden in Seele (blue) and Wille (green) variants
- **`--eva-glow-intensity`**: Multiplier (default `1`) — consumers set `0.5` for subdued, `1.5` for hot
- **`--eva-glow-depth-opacity`**: Controls depth shadow darkness (default `0.7`)

### New: `.eva-hud-glow` utility class (`hud-chrome.css`)
Signature backlit-edge treatment with 5 shadow layers: inner backlit edge, border glow, near bloom, mid bloom, and depth shadow. All driven by the tuning tokens. Drop it on any element to get the tactical display look.

### Consistency fixes — all chrome components now use tokens
Replaced hardcoded `rgba(204, 136, 0, ...)` glow values with `rgba(var(--eva-glow-rgb), calc(... * var(--eva-glow-intensity)))` in:
- **`hud-chrome.css`** — base `.eva-hud-chrome` shadow
- **`HudHeader.css`** — top lit edge, gold bloom, depth shadow
- **`HudSidebar.css`** — directional bloom (left/right variants)
- **`HudModal.css`** — double-border glow, header glow, depth layers
- **`HudDrawer.css`** — all 4 directional variants (left/right/top/bottom)
- **`HudAlert.css`** — info severity glow

### Bug fix: HudTooltip had no glow
`HudTooltip.css` only had a plain dark drop shadow (`0 4px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.8)`) — the only chrome component with zero glow treatment. Added subtle inner backlit edge + near bloom to match the family, while keeping it restrained (tooltips should be lightweight).

### What consumers can now do
```css
/* Subdued glow for a quieter UI */
.my-app { --eva-glow-intensity: 0.5; }

/* Hot tactical display */
.my-app { --eva-glow-intensity: 1.8; }

/* Per-element override */
.my-widget { --eva-glow-intensity: 0; } /* kill glow entirely */
```
